                     <td width="1%" class="TableCell"><img src="/images/spacer.gif" border="0"></td>
                     <td width="84%" class="TableCell"><b>
                           How does the search engine work on the FAQs?
                           </b></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td width="15%" class="TableCellAlternate" valign="top"><b>Answer:</b></td>
                     <td width="1%" class="TableCellAlternate"><img src="/images/spacer.gif" border="0"></td>
                     <td width="84%" class="TableCellAlternate">
                        The search engine is Lucene. It operates pretty much the same as Google, not quite a good though. You can use wildcards (e.g.
                        each*, or 1??), required words (+parlainth swordmaster - would only return faqs that have parlainth in them, and if swordmaster
                        is in there, that is a bonus - it will sort based on both being the highest result).<br />
                        
                     </td>
                  </tr>
